#  go-prompt distinctive features:
#    - EXECUTOR + COMPLETER pair — caller provides TWO callback
#      functions: `executor(string)` (called on Enter) and
#      `completer(prompt.Document) []prompt.Suggest` (called on
#      every keystroke for TAB-completion)
#    - `prompt.Suggest` struct — `{Text string, Description
#      string}` — appears in the completion dropdown
#    - `prompt.FilterHasPrefix` / `FilterContains` /
#      `FilterFuzzy` — built-in filter functions for narrowing
#      suggestions by the current input word
#    - `prompt.Document` — represents the current input state:
#      `GetWordBeforeCursor()`, `TextBeforeCursor()`,
#      `TextAfterCursor()`, etc. — for context-sensitive
#      completion
#    - OPTION-FUNCTION pattern (functional options) —
#      `prompt.New(exec, comp, OptionA, OptionB, ...)` with
#      typed Option* functions for configuration:
#      * `OptionPrefix("str ")` — static prompt prefix
#      * `OptionLivePrefix(fn)` — dynamic prefix (recomputed
#        each line)
#      * `OptionTitle("name")` — set terminal title
#      * `OptionHistory([]string)` — preload command history
#      * `OptionPrefixTextColor(Yellow)` / `OptionSuggestionBG
#        Color(DarkGray)` — color customization
#      * `OptionMaxSuggestion(10)` — limit suggestion count
#      * `OptionParser(parser)` — custom input tokenizer
#      * `OptionExitChecker(fn)` — function determining
#        whether to exit the REPL
#      * `OptionInputTextColor(...)` / `OptionSelectedBG
#        Color(...)` — fine-grained color tuning
